// Example asteroid bombardment (Q-2026-07-09-A; shape settled in the
// decisions log 2026-07-06): an impact is a tick-stamped, replay-recorded
// player action delivering a momentum + energy shock plus a particle
// payload. The payload "material" is quantity ranges — a region of quantity
// space, never a named substance; matter/energy arrive from outside the
// world by design, and the injection is exactly what the action declares.
//
//   genesis run    --actions scripts/bombardment.ron
//   genesis verify --actions scripts/bombardment.ron
//
// Two strikes: a heavy early impact seeding dense, energetic material into
// the world's center, then a light glancing strike on the far side (its
// payload arrives fast and diffuse). Works with any config — impacts
// reference no env fields.
(
    actions: [
        (
            tick: 500,
            action: Impact(
                x: 2048.0, y: 2048.0,
                radius: 64.0,
                impulse: 4.0,
                energy: 200.0,
                payload: (
                    count: 400,
                    matter: (lo: 0.5, hi: 1.5),
                    energy: (lo: 1.0, hi: 4.0),
                    information: (lo: 0.0, hi: 0.0),
                    speed: (lo: 0.1, hi: 0.8),
                    spread: 24.0,
                ),
            ),
        ),
        (
            tick: 1500,
            action: Impact(
                x: 512.0, y: 3584.0,
                radius: 32.0,
                impulse: 1.5,
                energy: 40.0,
                payload: (
                    count: 120,
                    matter: (lo: 0.1, hi: 0.4),
                    energy: (lo: 0.5, hi: 1.5),
                    information: (lo: 0.0, hi: 0.2),
                    speed: (lo: 1.0, hi: 3.0),
                    spread: 40.0,
                ),
            ),
        ),
    ],
)
